          "settings": {
            "heading": "<strong>Lift Stations/Pump Stations &Hydrogen Sulfide Issues</strong>",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_HmPAx9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Lift stations often end up functioning like unintended grease traps, as water sits long enough for <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/fog-education-and-training\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/fog-education-and-training\"><strong>FOG (Fats, Oils, and Grease)</strong></a> to cool, separate, and accumulate. This buildup typically coats the pumps, leading to overheating and disrupting the performance of float switches—ultimately causing system failures.</p><p><strong>Environmental Biotech’s customized lift station treatment programs</strong> are designed to target and break down FOG, helping extend the life of pumps and floats while improving overall efficiency. This means less energy usage, fewer breakdowns, and no unpleasant odors.</p><p>Our <strong>Bio Lift Systems</strong> introduce a blend of diffused oxygen and bio media to enhance the breakdown of FOG, organic solids, and other waste materials. The result is cleaner lift station operations, better odor control, and optimal system performance.</p><p>You’ll notice visible improvements within just one to two weeks.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
