    "image_with_text_RnXXQe": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_ctxYrg": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<strong>Lift/ Pump Station Management /Maintenance</strong>",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_xnpU3R": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Lift & Pump Station Maintenance and Management</strong></p><p>Any facility equipped with lift or pump stations understands the critical need for reliable operation. When these systems fail, it can lead to serious consequences—wastewater backups, property damage, and major disruptions for customers and operations.</p><p>Since pump stations operate in harsh, corrosive sewage environments, regular, preventative maintenance is essential to keep mechanical components functioning properly.</p><p><strong>Cleaning and FOG Control</strong></p><p>Sewage pump stations often experience heavy accumulation of non-biodegradable debris and <a href=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/fog-education-and-training\" title=\"https://environmentalbiotech.ca/pages/fog-education-and-training\">FOG (Fats, Oils, and Grease)</a>. Over time, these layers interfere with float switch performance and can allow items like rags or paper to pass through and damage pumps, leading to costly failures. Routine cleaning and FOG treatment are vital to prevent such issues.</p><p><strong>FOG Buildup and Equipment Failure</strong></p><p>FOG is a leading cause of pump station malfunction. It collects around floats, pump surfaces, and inside pipework or manifolds—accelerating wear and increasing the risk of system breakdowns.</p><p>As FOG management specialists, Environmental Biotech offers an effective solution with our BIO Lift system, which delivers live bacteria that actively digests FOG. At the same time, the system introduces diffused oxygen, helping reduce odors and keep your pump station running efficiently and reliably.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
