            "heading": "<strong>Hydrogen Sulfide Issues </strong>",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_y3Nqjy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Hydrogen sulfide (H₂S) is a serious problem in sewer systems—not only is the gas toxic, but it also leads to the formation of sulfuric acid, which corrodes pipes, pump stations, and critical infrastructure over time.</p><p>Environmental Biotech offers a specialized biological treatment program designed to reduce H₂S buildup effectively. This tailored solution can be applied in lift stations and sewer lines, delivering powerful results that improve safety and extend the life of your assets.</p><p>Ask us about our customized Bio Lift and H₂S control packages, designed to match your infrastructure needs. You'll experience more efficient lift station performance, reduced odors, less FOG accumulation, and fewer breakdowns—while keeping H₂S levels in check. A complete win-win for long-term operational health.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
